    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/674.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Newport</hi>, R. I.</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Am advised that buildings and furniture of Teresian and Jesus Maria Colleges in
                    Yucatan, Mexico, the property of Spanish subjects, <pb facs="1161" n="1045"
                        xml:id="pg_1045"/> have been confiscated. I request you earnestly to
                    interpose your influence to obtain restoration of property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
